tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows marked elevation of serum creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy with impaired concentrating ability. No evidence of urinary tract infection is present. Liver function and electrolytes are within normal limits. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and assessment for underlying causes of acute or chronic kidney disease.
